description: Features 3 "Seinfeld" episodes screened between 1990-1997. "The Busboy"; George tries to make it up to a busboy he has fired while Elaine risks life and limb to get rid of a visiting boyfriend. "The Baby Shower"; Kramer cons Jerry into having an illegal cable link. The day they instal the cable Elaine is hosting a baby shower in Jerry's apartment. One of the guests previously dated George and humilated him on a date. "The Hamptons"; Produced by Tom Gammill and Max Pross. Jerry, Elaine, Kramer, George and George's new girlfriend spend an eventful weekend at the holiday house of friends with an "ugly" baby. Everyone except George sees his new girlfriend baking topless, Kramer stumbles across a catch of lobsters, and George is caught in an embarrassing situation due to "shrinkage".
